void drive(double leftPow, double rightPow) {
  leftPow = max(min(leftPow, 1), -1);
  rightPow = max(min(rightPow, 1), -1);
  // -1<=leftPow<=1

  if (leftPow < 0) {
    digitalWrite(Tire_Left, LOW);
  } else {
    digitalWrite(Tire_Left, HIGH);
  }
  leftPow = abs(leftPow);

  if (rightPow < 0) {
    digitalWrite(Tire_Right, LOW);
  } else {
    digitalWrite(Tire_Right, HIGH);
  }
  rightPow = abs(rightPow);

  analogWrite(Speed_Left, (int) (leftPow * 255));
  analogWrite(Speed_Right, (int) (rightPow * 255));
}

The code here tells the car to put it's right "foot" in and shake it all about, the purpose of this is to have our car 
do the Hokey Pokey because we thought it would be pretty funny.

The next steps would probably be to add a buzzer that plays the music with the dancing, the only hard part would be 
timing the bot to the music.
